# Free-Threading Safety (Python 3.14t)

Comprehensive reference for writing thread-safe code in Bengal under Python 3.14t
(free-threaded, no GIL). This is the single source of truth for concurrency patterns.

**Works with**: `python.mdc`, `modules/architecture-patterns`, `modules/cost-annotations`

---

## Bengal's Concurrency Model

```
Build (sequential)                 Render (PARALLEL)           Finalization
┌──────────────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐
│ Discovery                │      │ Thread 1: page A    │     │ Thread 1     │
│ → Content                │      │ Thread 2: page B    │     │ Thread 2     │
│ → Parsing                │ ──── │ Thread 3: page C    │ ──→ │ ...          │
│ → Sections               │      │ ...                 │     │ Thread N     │
│ → Taxonomy               │      │ Thread N: page Z    │     └──────────────┘
│ → Snapshot               │      └─────────────────────┘
└──────────────────────────┘
 Phases 1–12.5 (single thread)    Phase 13+ (ThreadPoolExecutor)
```

**The core rule**: if data is read during the render phase, it must be safe for
concurrent access. "Safe" means either immutable or protected by a lock.

Build phases are sequential — mutable state is fine internally. The **frozen
boundary** is between snapshot (end of build) and render (start of parallel work).

---

## The Immutable Return Rule

`@cached_property` and `@property` accessed during render MUST return immutable types.

`functools.cached_property` writes to `instance.__dict__` without synchronization.
Two threads can race to compute and store the value. This is only safe if the
result is immutable — both threads compute identical values and the losing write
is harmless.

### Classification

| Return Type | Thread-Safe? | Action |
|---|---|---|
| `str`, `int`, `float`, `bool` | SAFE | No change needed |
| `tuple[X, ...]` | SAFE | Use instead of `list` |
| `frozenset[X]` | SAFE | Use instead of `set` |
| `frozen dataclass` | SAFE | Use instead of plain `dict` |
| `None` | SAFE | No change needed |
| `list[X]` | **UNSAFE** | Convert to `tuple(...)` |
| `set[X]` | **UNSAFE** | Convert to `frozenset(...)` |
| `dict[str, Any]` | **UNSAFE** | Convert to frozen dataclass |
| Mutable object | **UNSAFE** | Freeze or pre-warm |

### Known Properties Requiring Immutable Returns

These are accessed during parallel render on **shared objects** (Section, Site):

| Property | File | Current | Safe Type |
|---|---|---|---|
| `visibility` | `page/metadata.py` | `dict` | `VisibilitySettings` (frozen) |
| `regular_pages` | `section/queries.py` | `list` | `tuple[Page, ...]` |
| `sorted_pages` | `section/queries.py` | `list` | `tuple[Page, ...]` |
| `regular_pages_recursive` | `section/queries.py` | `list` | `tuple[Page, ...]` |
| `sorted_subsections` | `section/hierarchy.py` | `list` | `tuple[Section, ...]` |
| `subsection_index_urls` | `section/navigation.py` | `set` | `frozenset[str]` |
| `authors` | `page/__init__.py` | `list` | `tuple[Author, ...]` |
| `content_pages` | `section/ergonomics.py` | `list` | `tuple[Page, ...]` |

Page-level properties returning immutable values (str, int, bool) are safe even
without pre-warming because the race produces identical results.

