## Container Freeze Cheatsheet

| Mutable | Immutable Replacement | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `list[X]` | `tuple[X, ...]` | `tuple()` wraps any iterable |
| `set[X]` | `frozenset[X]` | `frozenset()` wraps any iterable |
| `dict` (fixed schema) | `@dataclass(frozen=True, slots=True)` | Named fields, type-checked |
| `dict` (dynamic keys) | `types.MappingProxyType(d)` | Read-only view of underlying dict |
| `dict` (never mutated) | Keep as `dict` | Safe if no writer; document it |

Templates iterate `tuple` and `frozenset` identically to `list` and `set` —
`{% for item in section.sorted_pages %}` works the same regardless of container type.

