## @cached_property vs @property Decision Tree

Use this when adding or reviewing properties in `bengal/core/`:

```
Is the property read during render (phase 13+)?
├── NO → @cached_property or @property with any return type is fine
└── YES
    ├── Does it return an immutable type (str, int, tuple, frozenset, frozen DC)?
    │   └── YES → @cached_property is safe (race produces identical values)
    └── Does it return a mutable type (list, set, dict)?
        ├── Can you change the return type to immutable (tuple, frozenset)?
        │   └── YES → Do that. This is the preferred fix.
        └── NO (e.g., external API constraint)?
            └── Pre-warm during snapshot phase so it's cached before render.

Is it on a shared object (Section, Site)?
├── YES → HIGH RISK — multiple threads access the same instance
└── NO (Page-level)
    └── LOWER RISK — typically one thread per page,
        but cross-references (page.related_posts[0].authors) exist
```

