## Validation Checklist

When reviewing code for free-threading safety:

- [ ] All `@cached_property` in `bengal/core/` return immutable types (or are pre-warmed)
- [ ] Module-level mutable dicts have lock-protected reads (not just writes)
- [ ] No `.clear()` eviction on shared caches (use LRU instead)
- [ ] Frozen boundary respected: no `list`/`set`/mutable-dict crossing build → render
- [ ] No `unittest.mock` imports in production modules
- [ ] No `json.dumps()` used solely for type validation
- [ ] Properties on shared objects (Section, Site) use immutable containers
- [ ] Config values read per-page are cached at pipeline init, not re-read from dict

